# ============================================================
# VERIXORA – .dockerignore
# ============================================================
# Summary:
#   This file tells Docker which files and folders to EXCLUDE
#   from the build context.  Docker normally copies everything
#   in the project folder before starting the build.  Excluding
#   unnecessary files:
#     - Speeds up the build (less data to transfer)
#     - Reduces the final image size
#     - Prevents secrets and local tools from leaking into
#       the image (security, ADR-031)
#   The patterns follow standard .gitignore syntax.
# ============================================================

# --- Version Control ---
# Git metadata is useless inside a container and could leak
# commit history.  Always exclude the whole .git folder.
**/.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Editor & IDE files ---
# These are developer-specific settings.  They must not be
# packaged into the container because they differ per user.
**/.vs
**/.vscode
**/.idea
*.user
*.suo
*.swp
*.sln.docstates

# --- Build artifacts (will be rebuilt inside Docker) ---
# The Dockerfile runs `dotnet restore` and `dotnet publish` itself.
# Copying existing bin/obj folders is wasteful and may contain
# binaries compiled for the wrong platform (e.g., Windows vs Linux).
**/bin
**/obj

# --- NuGet packages cache ---
# Packages are restored during `dotnet restore`.  We don't carry
# a local cache that might be stale or platform-specific.
**/packages

# --- Test projects ---
# Unit/integration tests are not needed at runtime.  Excluding them
# saves space and prevents test-specific configuration files from
# being included.
tests/

# --- Documentation & tools ---
# Markdown files, design docs, and the device simulator are not
# required for the running API.  The README is kept as an exception
# (it might be useful for a health-check landing page, but typically
# it's excluded as well).
docs/
tools/
*.md
!README.md            # Keep only the root README.md if desired

# --- Environment files & secrets (ADR-031) ---
# .env files and environment-specific appsettings.json files often
# contain secrets (connection strings, API keys).  They MUST be
# injected at runtime via a secrets manager, never baked into the image.
*.env
**/appsettings.*.json
!**/appsettings.json  # Keep the base template (no secrets)

# --- User secrets ---
# The `dotnet user-secrets` tool stores secrets in a JSON file on the
# developer's machine.  It must never end up in the container.
secrets.json

# --- Docker & Compose files ---
# Recursive Docker builds are dangerous.  Exclude the Dockerfile itself
# and any compose files to avoid confusion.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml

# --- Node / Frontend (if present) ---
# The mobile/web apps have their own build pipelines.  Their
# dependencies should not be in the backend image.
node_modules/
.npm
